caption: Love this place!  So so so fresh and the people are SO nice!! They deserve to flourish!  ORDER HERE!! You won't regret it!!

I have been coming here to get sushi burritos for a couple of years now and it never disappoints. I have even brought family and friends here before the pandemic and they loved it. The food is always fresh, consistent throught time and the place is very clean. The owners are always very friendly and they usually remember both my husband and I. Although we don't live as close we still try to get food from here when we can. Try it out it's so good, they have cooked options too if you don't like raw sushi amongst other dishes.

This restaurant is certainly one of the coolest place in the region. Every time I come to this place I am highly glad. They preserve their high  level service and the topmost level of food  they give. You no doubt will love this place. Warmly  recommended.
I love this place !!! Fresh ingredients and good food and a clean restaurant. The owners are so nice and welcoming. I’m definitely a new regular here.

last night was the first time we visited this magnificent restaurant. But It is obviously not the last time. We had great time with the efficient service, with the excellent cooking and fine drinks and with the comfortable charge. We will surely come back again.
I regularly come by purchasing some food in here. I love the speedy customer service and well prepared dishes. 5 stars from me.
Exceptional and flavorful food, I loved the character this spot has, and the workers were very nice. I will definitely come back again.

Love the sushi burrito! Only been here twice because it's far from where I live and I'm never in the area, but I mean I'd probably spend too much money here anyway. Haha. And the people working here have been very friendly! Definitely drop in

Hole-in-the-wall fast sushi and teriyaki joint operated by a really nice family who seem to work every hour of every day the place is open. There have been times I eat here twice a week. Great inexpensive sushi takeout any night of the week!

Good customer service and nice people but reviews are misleading. Egg rolls are tiny and sushi was also less than I expected. It wasn't terrible but I will definitely be looking for sushi elsewhere from now on.

We came to this restaurant for lunch. we heard about this restaurant from quite a few people.  Well, we were not disappointed. we were warmly welcomed by the crew  and we felt very good. The meal was great. We had a great time and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Recommended.
Love the owners and the sushi burritos are delicious
I visit this spot a lot since I work nearby. I must say the service is always excellent and they keep the place clean constantly. Rates are fair and they serve generous portions.
Stopped by for a quick lunch. Service was fast, the staff was friendly, food was delicious! 10/10

I went here to see how the food was based on the rating of this place and to be honest it was very good! The sushi was delicious and the wonton was good too (despite that i burned my mouth because they were kinda hot) and the people there are so nice i can't describe how i feeled with their kindness.  In short if you visit The Mall at PG and want to eat some good asian food this is the place for you.
Food was not as good as I thought and portions were small.

Originally I went with my husband a while back ago.   We were looking at other restaurants before we came across this restaurant.   We're decided to give it a try.  The restaurant is owned by a husband and wife plus daughter that also helps out.   The food was awesome. However, this time around we decided tip take the kids.   We ended up getting 5 sushi burritos and shrimp tempura.  My kids ended up loving the food. As usual the owners where very friendly and polite.   Such a relaxing atmosphere. At the end we ended up purchasing 2 more burritos. We definitely will be back
Great customer service & great food!!!
One of my favorite places in this area. I like to eat healthy and their sushi burritos are both super healthy AND really good.
I actually enjoyed their food and customer service, good area close to my house. The staff members are always very nice. Would recommend to others.

Super good sushi burrito. I would come here more if it was a little less expensive or more fish in the burrito. My go-to is the Spring Citrus Burrito, it is absolutely delicious, but wish it had a bit more salmon. My husband's favorite is the Dancing Twins, that one seems more filling. Will be back!

This is place has good Chinese food and sushi. I tried couple of dishes and the chicken was tender and crispy at the same time. My wife tried sushi and she said it was really good. Their bento combos are a great deal too if you want a main dish and 4 prices of sushi. The lady in the front was very friendly and polite. I definitely recommend this place. There is free parking for the first two hours in the public parking near to it.
Great food
I constantly stop getting some food in here. I loved the rapid service and well cooked food. 5 stars from me.
The sushi burrito was fresh and so tasty! Yum. I wish I lived closer. The owners were friendly people abd served us the best they could even though power was out for a bit.

Food was good, we ordered winning vegas sushi burritos, chicken teritaki and california rolls. $6 for 8 California rolls just as shown in the picture seems alright, but 6 tinny ones for $6 is a little bit overpriced.
Good restaurant nice owners good food
The small but energetic restaurant creates a homey feel. The staff is very nice and the food is great!
I absolutely love this place the food is amazing and they have EXCELLENT customer service!
Really fresh fish and a new take on sushi burritos. Definitely coming back for more .
The food is really good try their sushi burrito
Best place to eat in Hyattsville been going there since they opened and the owners are so sweet I love it here
Phenomenal food and great service.

A decent sushi place that feels very genuine. Owner operated and they are both very nice. The food is maybe a little bit above average, but not at all as great as the high ratings might make you believe. Still, if you want sushi in the area this is worth a visit.
I love their sushi but the chicken teriyaki with white rice wasn’t as great.
The sushi is AMAZINGG ! It’s all I ever get but they have a good variety and the owners are super friendly!!
Very fresh food. Sushi burritos are great and filling. The lunch specials are a good portion.
Amazing food
Local Family run place, best General Tso's In the DMV
Amazing service! Great food by the way.
I love their food. Its always fresh n made to order. Very friendly n the customer service is amazing.
Food was disgusting!! Not as ordered and no flavor.  Never again. If you like bad food,  this v is the place.
The stars tell truth. Best food in this area.
I was surprised to say one of the best places I've had sushi
Love the atmosphere,the food is always good. Haven't had any problems yet
One of my favorite places to eat
Love this place. Feel like I want to become friends with the owners, they are such a sweet couple.
Not a full sushi menu, but really good burrito style sushi rolls
I had the fighting terps burrito. It was really tasty.
I have been going here for awhile now and I can only say good things! Everything I have tried here so far has been amazing, but my favorite is the Chicken Teriyaki.

(Translated by Google) I was thinking about whether to go to Five Guys on the other side or come here, and then I had to come here and eat Asian food. I saw the star rating of 4.8, but I was worried because there weren't many people, but I got 2 stars / 3 stars for food !!!!!!!!! Really recommend !!!!!  (Original) 맞은편 파이브가이즈를 갈까 여기를 올까 고민하다가 굳이 여기까지와서 아시안 음식을 먹어야하나 싶어서 매우 고민했던 나 자신 반성하기를. 4.8의 별점을 보았지만 사람이 많지않아 고민했지만 중국인 아주머니와 아저씨의 인상에 별 2개 / 음식에 별 3개!!!!!!!!!! 진짜로 추천해요!!!!!
Really nice place to enjoy Asian food.

I'm sitting here right now. Just had the Chicken Teriyaki Bento Box. Quite tasty. This is a really nice small restaurant. Easy to find on America Blvd. Menu is not huge but it's quite ... interesting. They are evidently known for their Sushi Burritos. Sounds a bit gross but I guess they are good.  Not in an adventurous mood so I just went with a bento box. Came with four pieces of California Roll which were really good.  The staff is extremely friendly. I walked in and the very nice hostess asked if this was my first time here. "Yes." So she walked me quickly through the entire menu.  Will come again as it's a nice place, good food and they are very near my doctor's office.  Bottom line: Just go.
Good balance of veggies rice and meat in the sushi burritos. Clean environment, nice atnosphere, fast service. Recommend the sushi burritos
Super great sushi burrito that is pretty cheap
Great food,very clean place

At first, I was turned off by the idea of lettuce in the sushi burrito because I thought that they would use it as a filler, but I was fortunately very wrong.  The burritos have a very thin layer of rice (this is also a very good sign!) and HUGE sashimi chunks. The lettuce gives a nice crunch, and is used sparingly.  I highly recommend getting something with salmon in it. They don't use the cheap stuff. The salmon was so fatty and good.  The owner also gave me a free wonton with my order. She didn't speak English too well, but you can definitely tell this mom and pop shop has a huge customer focus that many places lack these days.
This family-run restaurant is very clean, and the food is made to order. Delicious sushi burrito rolls, my favorite is the #9.
The service here is A1; no one else will treat you better than the owners of this restaurant. Food taste great and is very fresh.
Absolutely wonderful.  The food is exquisite and fresh.  Highly recommended
Service was amazing and they were beyond friendly. Good was cooked hot and leftovers still taste bomb !!!

A nice, clean and quaint family owned restaurant. My wife and I came for the first time and the Fighting Terps was really good. They also gave us free wontons! Definitely a good place to get sushi burritos :)
Great food and great service!
Has delivery (via grubhub) but the food isn't mind blowing, not worth the price.
Great food and the best customer service in the DMV
Very good food must try at least once
I had the Terps burrito and I was a huge fan. Some of the sushi burrito places are pricey while burrito is pretty small. Sushiredo left me full and satisfied! Plus the owners are super sweet.
Every sushi burrito is amazing! I can't recommend this place enough. Tell your friends, coworkers anyone who will listen cause it's that good. Get the fighting terps burrito.

The food is good! In addition to sushi burritos they also have a regular menu of standard Japanese and standard American 'Chinese' fare. Lastly, there are a few comfortable tables and chairs inside (as well as outside),  so feel free to dine in, they're not just take out!
Awesome place. The sushi burritos with soy paper are great!
Super tasty!

Got the bento box, it was hot, delicious and very filling.My brother got the orange chicken. The cost was similar to take our places in the area but the quality was better.  The staff was also super nice. I'm definitely coming back for a suchi burrito

This is the only place to get a sushi burrito in the area. They have lots of options and good prices. The menu is otherwise limited but the place is brand new so I'm sure there's more to come. Food is made to order and service is super friendly. I will be a regular!
This place is so amazing! I love sushi so putting it in burrito form literally makes everything better. They are very nice as well.
Excellent, health conscious food. Great surprise... extremely clean environment that is inviting and welcoming. Keep it up!
Family vote was 5 stars. "Top notch" says the wife, and I happen to agree. Good food, well-lit, friendly!
The "Fighting Terp Roll" is amazing!

Me and my husband have had food from this delightful restaurant twice and we love it!! I had the crouching dragon and I adore the idea of a sushi burrito.  The salmon teriyaki was also very flavorful. I definitely recommend this restaurant.
Food was fast, fresh, and delicious! Fried cream cheese wontons were Amazing! I'll definitely be back soon!

This is a fun twist on sushi.  Basically they roll them like burritos.  One roll is the size of a relatively small burrito or about two regular sized sushi rolls.  We found the sushi to be very fresh and the family that runs it is very nice and clearly cares a great deal about delivering a quality product.
I ordered the Vegas sushiredo and it was really great! The salmon was fresh and the portion size is worth the price. Will be going there again soon!
